<h2><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="When_not_to_use_Archive::Zip"
>When not to use Archive::Zip</a></h2>

<p>If you are just going to be extracting zips (and/or other archives) you are recommended to look at using <a href="/perldoc?Archive%3A%3AExtract" class="podlinkpod"
>Archive::Extract</a> instead, as it is much easier to use and factors out archive-specific functionality.</p>

<h2><a class='u' href='#___top' title='click to go to top of document'
name="Try_to_avoid_IO::Scalar"
>Try to avoid IO::Scalar</a></h2>

<p>One of the most common ways to use Archive::Zip is to generate Zip files in-memory. Most people have use <a href="/perldoc?IO%3A%3AScalar" class="podlinkpod"
>IO::Scalar</a> for this purpose.</p>

<p>Unfortunately, as of 1.11 this module no longer works with <a href="/perldoc?IO%3A%3AScalar" class="podlinkpod"
>IO::Scalar</a> as it incorrectly implements seeking.</p>

<p>Anybody using <a href="/perldoc?IO%3A%3AScalar" class="podlinkpod"
>IO::Scalar</a> should consider porting to <a href="/perldoc?IO%3A%3AString" class="podlinkpod"
>IO::String</a>, which is smaller, lighter, and is implemented to be perfectly compatible with regular seekable filehandles.</p>

<p>Support for <a href="/perldoc?IO%3A%3AScalar" class="podlinkpod"
>IO::Scalar</a> most likely will <b>not</b> be restored in the future, as <a href="/perldoc?IO%3A%3AScalar" class="podlinkpod"
>IO::Scalar</a> itself cannot change the way it is implemented due to back-compatibility issues.</p>

